title: Delete policy and supporting pages code
body:
Policies are now published through the policy publisher.  Supporting pages are no longer a thing.

Later PRs will be raised to:
- Delete the data & tables
- Rename `Future::Policy` to `Policy`

Sorry for the Very Large Commits, but the nature of the change means doing it en masse was the only way to get it done in a reasonable time.

You *have* to review this commit by commit because Github can't display a diff longer than 300 files.

The true changeset is `356 files changed, 792 insertions(+), 5874 deletions(-)`.

Good luck!

https://trello.com/c/nZiu3ExT/270-remove-policies-and-supporting-pages-from-whitehall

title: Remove references to archived
body:
Now that we are no longer moving editions into an archived state and we
have updated all archived editions to be in a withdrawn state we should
remove references to archived.

---

This shouldn't be merged until after the data migration in https://github.com/alphagov/whitehall/pull/2210 has been run.

title: Upgrade Ruby to 2.2.2
body:
A few gem upgrades:
- kgio 2.8.0 wasn't compatible
- raindrops 0.11.0 wasn't compatible
- babosa had a duplicated key in a hash, which Ruby 2.2 has a warning for

In one of our tests, we were defining a key twice in the same hash, causing a warning. This has been fixed.
